constraint.description: Property 32: Real interval with values restricted to [0-100]

constraint.name: creationDateTime_Type
constraint.description: Property Creation Date and Time: Length: 20 -- Formatted in accordance with ISO 8601:2000, 5.4.1, Combinations of date and time of day - Complete representation - Extended format, a calendar date and time representation, as a single data element comprising up to twenty characters, where [YYYY] represents a calendar year, [MM] the ordinal number of a calendar month within the calendar year, [DD] the ordinal number of a day within the calendar month, [hh] the ordinal number of an hour within the calendar day, [mm] the ordinal number of a minute within the hour, [ss] the ordinal number of a second within the minute, and an optional 'Z' when the time is according to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), as 'YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ' (for example: '1985-04-12T11:45:20Z' for 11 hours, 45 minutes and 20 seconds UTC on 12 April 1985). Representations with reduced precision may be used in accordance with 5.4.2 (for example: '1985-04-12' for 12 April 1985). Representations consistently using basic format (eliminating the hyphen '-' and the colon ':') may be used in accordance with 5.4.1 (for example: '19850412T114520Z').

Value.definition: The use of this enumerant depends on the choice of modeling implementation for 'Union' datatypes. Where the 'Union' may not be directly expressed and instead two 'storage locations' are specified, then it becomes necessary that the 'reason storage location' should be able to unambiguously express that the 'value storage location' does, indeed, have a value specified. Where the 'Union' may be directly expressed as a single 'storage location' then it is unnecessary (and not physically possible) to express that the 'value is specified' at the same time that a value is, indeed, specified.
